[code=php]<?php
header ("Content-type: image/Gif");
$back = imagecreatefromgif ("back.gif");
$textcolor = ImageColorAllocate ($back, 10, 10, 10);
$time = $date = date("H:i");
ImageString ($back, 10, 150, 100, "Last Refresh at: $time", $textcolor);
ImageGif ($back);
ImageDestroy ($back);
?>
[/code]

explain:
[code=php]header ("Content-type: image/Gif");[/code]
make the file be read as a gif image

[code=php]$back = imagecreatefromgif ("back.gif");[/code]make the image bassed on this one. you can change the back.gif to the source of your image
must be a gif, you can use a jpg or png with these functions:
imagecreatefromjpeg ();
imagecreatefrompng ();
you will also have to change the header to image/jpeg or image/png

[code=php]$textcolor = ImageColorAllocate ($back, 80, 80, 60);[/code]
set a new color, in this case its for our text.. $back.. the image 
color strengths: 80, 80, 60.. red, green, blue..

[code=php]ImageString ($back, 10, 150, 100, "Last Refresh at: $time", $textcolor);[/code]
set a sting on the image (in my case i use the time)
cords: 10, 150, 100.. size, x, y

[code=php]ImageGif ($back);[/code]
show the image

[code=php]ImageDestroy ($back);[/code]
destroy the tmp file

